ies plus Sky Sports and BT Sport domestically. That is different to both Germany and Spain, where £262m and £228m is still owed. Vanguard The Premier League could be set for a pay cut after eye-watering back-to-back domestic TV deals but experts say the boom times are far from over for English football. February 14, 2018 In "Sports" English champions Chelsea received a record Premier League pay-out of more than £150 million ($190 million, 172 million euros) this season, nearly £60 million more than their predecessors Leicester, after new TV deals came into force. June 2, 2017 In "News" Premier League clubs have approved the controversial move to give departing chief executive Richard Scudamore a £5 million ($6.3 million) farewell gift. November 15, 2018 In "Sports"